members.name: on
members.description: The event name to monitor for, from previous non-petalian element.

members.name: to
members.description: css pattern to match for from downstream siblings.

members.name: careOf
members.description: CSS Selector to use to select single child within the destination element.

members.name: ifTargetMatches
members.description: Only act on event if target element css-matches the expression specified by this attribute.

members.name: prop
members.description: Name of property to set on matching (downstream) siblings.

members.name: propFromEvent
members.description: Dynamically determined name of property to set on matching (downstream) siblings from event object.

members.name: val
members.description: Specifies path to JS object from event, that should be passed to downstream siblings.  Value of '.' passes entire entire object.

members.name: observe
members.description:
Specifies element to latch on to, and listen for events.
Searches previous siblings, parent, previous siblings of parent, etc.
Stops at Shadow DOM boundary.

members.name: fireEvent
members.description: Artificially fire event on target element whose name is specified by this attribute.

members.name: initEvent
members.description: In some cases, the initVal can only be obtained after initEvent fires

members.name: capture
members.description: A Boolean indicating that events of this type will be dispatched to the registered listener before being dispatched to any EventTarget beneath it in the DOM tree.
